{"lemma":"عَقِيم","slug":"عَقِيم","root":"ع.ق.م","root_slug":"ع-ق-م","root_link":"/words/roots/ع-ق-م","pos":"ADJ","pos_camel":"adj","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"عَقِيم","root":"عقم","pos":"N","occurrence_count":4},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["adj"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":3},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n30019"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B9%D9%8E%D9%82%D9%90%D9%8A%D9%85"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"adj","gloss":"infertile, unproductive"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"barren, sterile"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"pointless, ineffectual","examples":[{"text":"نِقَاش عَقِيم","english":"a sterile debate, a pointless discussion"}]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"فَعِيل (faʕīl)-type stative-verb derived from the active participle from the verb عَقُمَ (ʕaquma, “to be sterile”)."},"ipa":["/ʕa.qiːm/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n30019","headword_ar":"عَقِيمٌ","root":"Eqm","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) with which ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaqaAmN","text_ar":"عَقَامٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"is syn., (S,) is applied to a womb, meaning ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Barren;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"incapable of receiving offspring, in consequence of a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hazomap","text_ar":"هَزْمَة"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"therein;"},{"kind":"text","text":"[see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EuqomN","text_ar":"عُقْمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":";] as also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaqiymapN","text_ar":"عَقِيمَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maEoquwmapN","text_ar":"مَعْقُومَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (K;) the last of which is expl. by Ks as signifying, thus applied,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"bound,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"constricted;"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ma$oduwdapN","text_ar":"مَشْدُودَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; so in some copies of the S, and in the TA;) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"obstructed;"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"masoduwdapN","text_ar":"مَسْدُودَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; so in other copies of the S;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that will not bring forth offspring."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, TA.) It is also applied to a woman, (IAar, S, Msb, K,) as meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Barren; that will not bring forth offspring:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar, Msb, TA:) so in a trad. cited voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^asowaA^u","text_ar":"اَسْوَاُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"swA^","text_ar":"سوا"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaqaAy^imu","text_ar":"عَقَايِمُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EuqumN","text_ar":"عُقُمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Msb,) and sometimes"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EuqomN","text_ar":"عُقْمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, and so in some copies of the K instead of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EuqumN","text_ar":"عُقُمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":",) a contraction of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EuqumN","text_ar":"عُقُمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S.) And it is also applied to a man, meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"To whom no child is born;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, K;) and so ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaqaAmN","text_ar":"عَقَامٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EuqamaA='u","text_ar":"عُقَمَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EiqAmN","text_ar":"عِقامٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaqomaY","text_ar":"عَقْمَى"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K.) ―         -b2-  [Hence,] applied to a wind, (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such as does not fecundate,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fructify;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that does not cause clouds to produce rain, nor trees to produce fruit;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S;) i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that does not bring rain, but is destructive:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that does not fructify the trees, nor raise clouds, nor bear rain."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alr~iyHu AlEaqiymu","text_ar":"الرِّيحُ العَقِيمُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[mentioned in the Kur li. 41] means (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The west,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"westerly, wind, by means of which"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the tribe of"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"'Ád were destroyed."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b3-  Applied to intellect ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaqolN","text_ar":"عَقْلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"), it means (assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Barren,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"unprofitable to him who possesses it:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"unfruitful of good."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b4-  As applied to speech, or language, see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EuqomiY~N","text_ar":"عُقْمِىٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kalimaAtN EuqumN","text_ar":"كَلِمَاتٌ عُقُمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"means (assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Words,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"expressions,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sentences,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"strange,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"difficult to understand."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b5-  It is applied to a day as meaning (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Without air"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wind"},{"kind":"text","text":"],"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and therefore"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sultry,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"intensely hot."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb.) ―         -b6-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EuqaAmN","text_ar":"عُقَامٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b7-  And see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaqaAmN","text_ar":"عَقَامٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b8-  The day of resurrection is termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yawomN EaqiymN","text_ar":"يَوْمٌ عَقِيمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"because [it is (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A day"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having no day after it."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, TA.) Accord. to some, it is thus termed in the Kur xxii. 54. (Bd &c.) ―         -b9-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ald~unoyaA EaqiymN","text_ar":"الدُّنْيَا عَقِيمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"means (assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The present world"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"does not render good to him who is of the people thereof."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b10-  And one says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Almuloku EaqiymN","text_ar":"المُلْكُ عَقِيمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"meaning (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Dominion is a condition in which,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, K, TA,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the seeking of which,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"relationship profits not,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, Msb, K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"nor friendship:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb:) for a man will slay his son, (S, Msb,) if he fear him, (S,) and his father, (Msb,) for dominion; (S, Msb;) or because, in seeking it, the father will be slain, and the son, and the brother, and the paternal uncle; (Th, K;) or because, in it, the ties of relationship are severed by slaughter and by undutiful conduct. (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["K","S","IAar","Msb","TA","A"]}]}}